\pard\ql\f1\fs30\sb180\sa180\cf1\keepn\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw12\brdrcf2\brsp80\b 1  Executive summary\b0\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 THOG2 stores compact spectral coefficients and materialises dense-equivalent transformer weights when they are needed. The Remainder Architecture Enhancement adds a second learned representation: one signed low-bit correction code for each covered materialised weight position.\par
\pard\sb100\sa170\li180\ri180\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrl\brdrs\brdrw28\brdrcf2\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\shading100\cbpat3\f0\fs22 \b One weight consumed by the transformer\b0\line \f2\fs19 effective_weight = decoded_adjacent_value(base_weight, remainder_value)\f0\fs22\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 The transformer still uses one effective weight matrix. The enhancement does not add a second network, a second loss or a second backward pass. It adds a compact local correction to the weight produced by the existing spectral representation.\par
