\pard\sb110\sa170\li180\ri180\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrl\brdrs\brdrw28\brdrcf2\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\shading100\cbpat8\f0\fs22 \b Central engineering difficulty\b0\line The forward idea is simple. The difficult part is a custom optimiser that converts a continuous rejected gradient into bounded integer code changes without recreating dense per-weight optimiser state.\par
\pard\sb110\sa170\li180\ri180\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrl\brdrs\brdrw28\brdrcf2\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\shading100\cbpat6\f0\fs22 \b Buildability statement\b0\line This specification fixes the baseline decoder, address model, gradient split, reference optimiser, target optimiser, update ordering, checkpoint state, tests and stop rules. An implementer should not need to invent architecture.\par
