\pard\ql\f1\fs30\sb180\sa180\cf1\keepn\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw12\brdrcf2\brsp80\b 2  Purpose, authority and scope\b0\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\cf1\keepn\b 2.1  Purpose\b0\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 This document defines the behaviour that the Remainder Architecture Enhancement must implement. It is normative for architecture, data ownership, numerical meaning, optimiser behaviour, lifecycle state and acceptance testing.\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\cf1\keepn\b 2.2  Relationship to the implementation plan\b0\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 The companion Implementation Plan describes the order in which this specification should be built. Where the two documents differ, this Requirements Specification is authoritative for required behaviour. The Implementation Plan must be updated rather than silently overriding this document.\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\cf1\keepn\b 2.3  Initial model coverage\b0\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 The first implementation applies only to spectrally generated two-dimensional transformer weight matrices.\par
