\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\cf1\keepn\b 6.3  Straight-through derivative for the base value\b0\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 The decoded choice is discrete. During forward execution, the effective value is the decoded adjacent-representable value. During backward, the local derivative with respect to base_weight is treated as one before the gradient-routing hook replaces the incoming gradient with the projectable component.\par
\pard\sb100\sa170\li180\ri180\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrl\brdrs\brdrw28\brdrcf2\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\shading100\cbpat3\f0\fs22 \f2\fs19 decoded = decode_adjacent(base_weight, remainder_value, effective_dtype)\line effective_weight = base_weight + stop_gradient(decoded - base_weight)\f0\fs22\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\cf1\keepn\b 6.4  Directional code-step size\b0\par
