\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\cf1\keepn\b 10.3  Convert the rejected gradient to code space\b0\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 First determine the direction in which the code should move to reduce the loss. Then multiply the rejected weight gradient by the actual numeric distance represented by one code step in that direction.\par
\pard\sb100\sa170\li180\ri180\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrl\brdrs\brdrw28\brdrcf2\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\shading100\cbpat3\f0\fs22 \f2\fs19 intended_direction = -sign(G_remainder)\line G_code = G_remainder * directional_step\line G_code = mask_outward_movement_at_bounds(G_code)\f0\fs22\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\cf1\keepn\b 10.4  Update factored second moments\b0\par
\pard\sb100\sa170\li180\ri180\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrl\brdrs\brdrw28\brdrcf2\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\shading100\cbpat3\f0\fs22 \f2\fs19 row_observation = mean(G_code ** 2, across columns)\line column_observation = mean(G_code ** 2, across rows)\line row_moment = beta2 * row_moment + (1 - beta2) * row_observation\line column_moment = beta2 * column_moment + (1 - beta2) * column_observation\f0\fs22\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\cf1\keepn\b 10.5  Form the adaptive normaliser\b0\par
\pard\sb100\sa170\li180\ri180\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrl\brdrs\brdrw28\brdrcf2\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\shading100\cbpat3\f0\fs22 \f2\fs19 normaliser = outer(row_moment, column_moment) / max(mean(row_moment), eps)\line U = G_code / sqrt(normaliser + eps)\f0\fs22\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 The outer product reconstructs a low-rank approximation to a dense per-coordinate second moment. It is not expected to equal full Adam, but it supplies per-row and per-column adaptation without dense state.\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\cf1\keepn\b 10.6  Clip and request code movement\b0\par
\pard\sb100\sa170\li180\ri180\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrl\brdrs\brdrw28\brdrcf2\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\shading100\cbpat3\f0\fs22 \f2\fs19 U = U / max(1, rms(U) / clip_threshold)\line delta_code = clamp(-remainder_lr * U, -1, +1)\f0\fs22\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\cf1\keepn\b 10.7  Stochastic integer update\b0\par
\pard\sb100\sa170\li180\ri180\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrl\brdrs\brdrw28\brdrcf2\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\shading100\cbpat3\f0\fs22 \f2\fs19 probability = abs(delta_code)\line integer_step = sign(delta_code) when uniform_random < probability; otherwise 0\line remainder_values = clamp(remainder_values + integer_step, q_min, q_max)\f0\fs22\par
\pard\sb110\sa170\li180\ri180\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrl\brdrs\brdrw28\brdrcf2\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\shading100\cbpat7\f0\fs22 \b No dense momentum in the baseline\b0\line A dense first-moment matrix is prohibited in R2. If experiments prove momentum essential, the next allowed investigation is block-shared or low-rank momentum, not silent reintroduction of dense state.\par
